## Field reference

| attribute | constraints |
|---|---|
| `name` | Required. 1-128 characters. Unique. |
| `description` | Optional. Up to 255 characters. Defaults to `""`. |
| `enabled` | Optional. Boolean. Defaults to `true`. |
| `patterns` | Optional. Ordered list of pattern objects (see below). **Order is significant** — evaluation merges them in order. Defaults to an empty list. |
| `is_builtin` | Read-only. `true` for built-in ACLs. |

### `patterns[]` object fields

Each element of the `patterns` list is an object with these fields:

| field | type | required | default | constraints |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `pattern` | string | **yes** | — | 1-512 characters. |
| `type` | string | no | `glob` | One of the `type` values below. |

### `patterns[].type` values

| type | meaning |
|---|---|
| `glob` | Shell-style glob match (the default). |
| `regex` | Regular-expression match. |

## Notes

- **Read is via the list endpoint.** The backend exposes no GET-single route for
  ACLs, so the provider reads an ACL by listing and filtering on `id`. If the ACL
  is absent from the list it is treated as deleted.
- **Built-in ACLs cannot be managed.** An ACL with `is_builtin = true` cannot be
  edited or deleted; the API rejects such operations. Do not manage built-in ACLs
  with Terraform.
- **Deletion is refused while referenced.** The API refuses to delete an ACL that
  is still referenced by a session-policy rule's `command_acl_ids`; remove the
  reference first.

